At everyone, found a workaround to issue https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/119623#issuecomment-1535669615

Sorry, but I have no time to add it to our public class but anyone who needs it can do it this way:
1) Wrap the text inside Padding, you can copy/paste this snippet. 
```
WidgetSpan(
  baseline: TextBaseline.ideographic,
  alignment: PlaceholderAlignment.top,
  child: Builder(builder: (context) {
    return Transform.translate(
      //Emoji baseline will be off-center after increasing its size, Offset will
      //fix baseline to look native-like
      offset: Offset(0, emojiOffsetMultiplier),
      // Correct issue with emoji not being centered on iOS
      // https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/119623#issuecomment-1535669615
      child: Padding(
        padding: (Platform.isIOS) ?
            EdgeInsets.only(left:1)
            :
            EdgeInsets.only(left:0),
        child:Text(
        e,
        style: emojiStyle,
        maxLines: maxLines,
        overflow: overflow,
      ),),
    );
  }),
),
```

2) Now that you shifted the emoji to the right in order to fix above issue, you must compensate this change by reducing of 1px the `letterSpacing` inside `text_widget_utils_IOS.dart`.
3) This would be enough for most cases. But to those who also needs `TextWidget` to overflow with breaking-words (ie. chat bubbles UI), you must fix this issue too https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/61081. To do it, use `runes` to add an invisible white space breaking-word '\u200B'. Now text will overflow/wrap correctly but you will see a small space between chars. To compensate it, adjust `letterSpacing` inside `text_widget_utils_IOS.dart` (as in point 2).

Final result is close to native.
However, we found no way to workaround https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/120857 coz it is out of our reach.
If flutter team can fix it, we will finally have a real workaround for text on iOS meantime it becomes production-ready. Until that moment, we don't feel comfy to show our app to users.

Hello guys, would be great if we could fix this issue during next weeks.
As we know, wrong emojis size and off-center emojis https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/119623 is a real pain for Flutter apps, coz almost all texts typed in on a phone contain an emoji.

We provided a workaround here https://github.com/delfme/text-widget, along with a sample code that can be useful for testing fixes in a multiline scenario. In our case, several manipulations must be performed on the text and that affects performance if not done at engine level. Also, we noticed that `textPainter.width` provides a wrong result when emojis are inside the text, which means that we currently cannot determine the correct width of a text (which is a much needed func).

@gnprice does this https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/28894#issuecomment-1828630104 take into account the required changes to emojis `Offset` after emoji size is increased? Coz increasing the emoji `fontSize` inside a line must be compensated via `Offset` to avoid to break baseline. This is indeed the hack that Apple is doing. They also hack the emoji `letterSpacing`, coz user might type several emojis in a row like this: "😊😊😊" and that `WidgetSpan` uses a specific `letterSpacing` that varies based on `fontSize`.

@dnfield @jonahwilliams is there a reason why we cannot just replicate at engine level the fix from https://github.com/delfme/text-widget ?

