@dnfield why can't we adopt the approach you mentioned here with the discovery made in our repo ? https://github.com/delfme/text-widget
As mentioned, issue is size, kernel and offset (when text is multiline) but can't we just ask Skia to manipulate those parameters as we do inside `text-widget`? In case, I can provide more precise numbers, we kept tuning things up.

I kindly disagree with those who mentioned they'd rather not fix issue this way coz it looks like a patch. I mean, meantime there is no perfect fix, it is way better to have something for the users. Also, several text-related issues are intertwined. For example, I lately filed this https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/151952 where I think `textPainter` might be returning width values that are not very precise when emojis are inside text (prolly due to emojis' wrong kernel and size).

One last consideration is about iphone users: they notice UI fidelity issues in one second, and are quick to mark an app like "cheap" or uninstall it.
